# Custom Metadata RECORDS are deployed via `make sf-seed-runbooks`
# (scripts/seed_runbook_cmdt.sh, Apex Metadata API) — NOT `sf project deploy`.
#
# afm-dev hits a known Salesforce platform bug (GACK -315522575): ANY
# CustomMetadata record deploy through the Metadata API fails with
# "UNKNOWN_EXCEPTION: An unexpected error occurred" — org-wide and
# content-independent (a one-field record fails; SOAP and REST; API 60-66; a
# brand-new clean CMDT type fails identically). The CMDT type+fields and all
# non-CMDT metadata deploy fine. Excluding the records here keeps
# `make sf-deploy` / `make sf-validate` (which deploy all of force-app) working;
# seed the records with `make sf-seed-runbooks`.
#
# The customMetadata/*.md-meta.xml files remain the canonical source and would
# deploy normally on an unaffected org — drop this entry if the GACK is resolved
# (e.g. via a Salesforce support case). See _private/docs/build/07_agentforce.md
# (Decisions log) and memory afm-dev-cmdt-mdapi-deploy-broken.
**/customMetadata/**

# Agentforce Bot / BotVersion / GenAiPlannerBundle are publish-generated by
# `sf agent publish authoring-bundle` (one set per published version). The
# aiAuthoringBundle/*.agent is the version-controlled source of truth (TARS
# pattern); the generated metadata is a build artifact — excluded so
# `make sf-deploy` / `sf-validate` (which deploy all of force-app) stay clean.
# `sf agent publish` regenerates + activates the agent.
**/bots/**
**/genAiPlannerBundles/**
